sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor H as Human<br/>author and decider
  participant K as cc-iasd kernel<br/>state machine + guards
  participant PL as planner<br/>authoring role
  participant RV as reviewer<br/>fresh-context role
  participant WK as worker<br/>implementation role
  participant J as journal + evidence<br/>tool-owned
  participant Src as src/<br/>artifact repos

  Note over K,J: All progress is a guard-passing transition recorded in journal. Roles return judgment only; the kernel drives ordering.

  rect rgb(238, 244, 255)
    Note over H,J: planning: authoring and spec gate
    H->>K: new vision / spec / charter
    K->>PL: launch planner for authored content
    PL-->>K: authored vision / spec / charter
    K-->>J: created / revised events
    K->>PL: propose gap resolution when unresolved
    PL-->>K: gap add (background / options / recommendation)
    K-->>J: gap.opened event
    K->>RV: launch reviewer for spec gate (fresh context)
    RV-->>K: spec review record (verdict + findings)
    K-->>J: review.recorded event
    K->>K: spec ready guard (sections / gap 0 / vision approved / hash match)
  end

  rect rgb(240, 248, 240)
    Note over H,J: launch gate and campaign launch
    K->>RV: launch reviewer for launch gate (fresh context)
    RV-->>K: launch review record
    K-->>J: review.recorded event
    K->>K: campaign launch guard (charter / coverage ready / depends_on closed)
    K-->>J: transitioned campaign to active
  end

  rect rgb(255, 250, 235)
    Note over H,Src: run open / handoff and worker implementation
    K->>K: run open guard (campaign active / task open / handoff synth)
    K->>K: compile handoff from upstream artifacts
    alt handoff synthesis fails
      K-->>J: run open rejected (missing sections listed)
      Note over K: upstream-deficient run does not start; no guesser exists
    else handoff synthesis succeeds
      K->>WK: hand off compiled context to worker
      WK->>Src: implement within surface scope
      WK-->>K: notes appended / gap add on scope conflict
      K-->>J: note.appended / gap.opened events
      K->>K: run return (measure git diff snapshot)
      K->>Src: run verify (execute Checks as child process)
      K-->>J: verify.recorded (verdict + surface match)
    end
  end

  rect rgb(248, 240, 248)
    Note over H,J: run gate and termination
    K->>RV: launch reviewer for run gate (fresh context)
    RV-->>K: run review record
    K-->>J: review.recorded event
    alt accept (verification pass + review + gap 0)
      K->>K: run accept guard
      K-->>J: transitioned run to accepted
    else block (cheapest legal exit)
      K-->>J: backtrack request generated, run blocked
      Note over K: block is cheaper than faking completion (cost gradient)
    else escalate (needs human decision)
      K-->>J: escalation packet generated, run escalated
      K->>H: escalation packet (options / impact / resume condition)
      H->>K: decide (actor=human stamped)
      K-->>J: decision.recorded event
    end
  end

  rect rgb(240, 244, 250)
    Note over H,J: completion gate and campaign close
    K->>RV: launch reviewer for completion gate (fresh context)
    RV-->>K: completion review record
    K-->>J: review.recorded event
    K->>H: completion report + completion review
    H->>K: campaign close (human acceptance)
    K->>K: campaign close guard (all runs accepted / completion review / gaps resolved / report exists)
    K-->>J: transitioned campaign to closed
  end
